{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticrwlock"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"only one writer may write at a time.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"StaticRWLock","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Take a look at the following example:"}]},{"code":["  GStaticRWLock rwlock = G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT;","  GPtrArray *array;","","  gpointer","  my_array_get (guint index)","  {","    gpointer retval = NULL;","","    if (!array)","      return NULL;","","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock (&rwlock);","    if (index < array->len)","      retval = g_ptr_array_index (array, index);","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock (&rwlock);","","    return retval;","  }","","  void","  my_array_set (guint index, gpointer data)","  {","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_lock (&rwlock);","","    if (!array)","      array = g_ptr_array_new ();","","    if (index >= array->len)","      g_ptr_array_set_size (array, index + 1);","    g_ptr_array_index (array, index) = data;","","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock (&rwlock);","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows an array which can be accessed by many readers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_get()"},{"type":"text","text":" function) simultaneously, whereas the writers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_set()"},{"text":" function) will only be allowed once at a time","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and only if no readers currently access the array. This is because"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the potentially dangerous resizing of the array. Using these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions is fully multi-thread safe now."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Most of the time, writers should have precedence over readers. That","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"means, for this implementation, that as soon as a writer wants to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lock the data, no other reader is allowed to lock the data, whereas,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of course, the readers that already have locked the data are allowed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to finish their operation. As soon as the last reader unlocks the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"data, the writer will lock it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Even though ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is not opaque, it should only be used"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with the following functions.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_rw_lock_* functions can be used even if"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" has not been called. Then they do nothing, apart"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from g_static_rw_lock_*_trylock, which does nothing but returning ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A read-write lock has a higher overhead than a mutex. For example, both","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to lock and unlock a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", so it takes at least twice the time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to lock and unlock a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" that it does to lock and unlock a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". So only data structures that are accessed by multiple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"readers, and which keep the lock for a considerable time justify a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". The above example most probably would fare better with a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GStaticRWLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticRWLock"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticRWLock"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]}]}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-33hto","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-3kcsg","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-3zz8s","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-5u2m3","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-8mhsi","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(gconstpointer: